definition.value: An imidazolidine-2,4-dione that is 5-aminohydantoin in which a carbamoyl group is attached to the exocyclic nitrogen.
An optically active form of allantoin having (R)-(-)-configuration.
An optically active form of allantoin having (S)-(+)-configuration.
A glycosylglucose consisting of a beta-D-xylopyranose residue and an alpha-D-glucopyranose residue joined in sequence by a (1->6) glycosidic bond.
